      "message": "Calling fork inside a multi-threaded process is risky if any of the other threads might be holding locks when the fork happens because it would cause a deadlock in the child process. Because of this we check if the process is single threaded before allowing fork_remap (except for cfg(test)). It probably makes sense to revisit that and not even allow it for cfg(test) since using a custom test runner lets us force the test to be one thread.",
